19/12/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria and Turkey agree on the need for co-operation in the fight against terrorism, said Parliamentary Speaker Ognyan Gerdzhikov and the chairman of the Turkish Parliament's Foreign Relations Committee, Mehmet Dulger, who visited Sofia on Thursday (18 December). They stressed that the November terror attacks in Turkey underscore the importance of united efforts and action against international terrorism. Gerdzhikov said one of Bulgaria's priorities, as chairman of the OSCE next year, would be combating terrorism. (BTA, BNT - 18/12/03)
